? How to proceed with docker file optimisation  = faster to pull , push and  deploy 
- though the use of multi stage builds 
- making image lighter 


Multi stage builds allow us to use multiple FROM statements in docker file : 

- Using one stage to build your application  and a much lighter stage to create the final image you deploy

- This process allows for removing off unnecessary dependancies = creating a smaller optimised image - quicker to pull from a registry / deploy 

Check size of image with = docker images my-flask-app:original 

#stage1 to build the app

FROM python 3.14 as build 
WORKDIR /app

RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
    build-essential \
    pkg-config \
    default-libmysqlclient-dev \
    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

COPY . . 

RUN pip install --no-cache-dir flask mysqlclient


#stage2 : production stage 

FROM python:3.14
WORKDIR /app 

COPY —from=Build  /app /app 

EXPOSE 5002

CMD [“python” , “”app.py”]

Docker built -t my-flask-app:multistage .

Docker images my-flask-app:multistage = shows the image has reduced in size 

*change the image name in docker compose file to my-flask-app:multistage * 

Docker compose up -d 

